descr: "A definition of a FHIR structure. This resource is used to describe the underlying resources, data types defined in FHIR, and also for describing extensions and constraints on resources and data types."

fields.name: resourceType
fields.descr: "This is a StructureDefinition resource"

fields.name: url
fields.descr: "An absolute URI that is used to identify this structure definition when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance. This SHALL be a URL, SHOULD be globally unique, and SHOULD be an address at which this structure definition is (or will be) published. The URL SHOULD include the major version of the structure definition. For more information see [Technical and Business Versions](resource.html#versions)."

fields.name: _url
fields.descr: "Extensions for url"

fields.name: identifier
fields.descr: "A formal identifier that is used to identify this structure definition when it is represented in other formats, or referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance."

fields.name: version
fields.descr: "The identifier that is used to identify this version of the structure definition when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or instance. This is an arbitrary value managed by the structure definition author and is not expected to be globally unique. For example, it might be a timestamp (e.g. yyyymmdd) if a managed version is not available. There is also no expectation that versions can be placed in a lexicographical sequence."

fields.name: _version
fields.descr: "Extensions for version"

fields.name: name
fields.descr: "A natural language name identifying the structure definition. This name should be usable as an identifier for the module by machine processing applications such as code generation."

fields.name: _name
fields.descr: "Extensions for name"

fields.name: title
fields.descr: "A short, descriptive, user-friendly title for the structure definition."

fields.name: _title
fields.descr: "Extensions for title"

fields.name: status
fields.descr: "The status of this structure definition. Enables tracking the life-cycle of the content."

fields.name: _status
fields.descr: "Extensions for status"

fields.name: experimental
fields.descr: "A boolean value to indicate that this structure definition is authored for testing purposes (or education/evaluation/marketing), and is not intended to be used for genuine usage."

fields.name: _experimental
fields.descr: "Extensions for experimental"

fields.name: date
fields.descr: "The date  (and optionally time) when the structure definition was published. The date must change if and when the business version changes and it must change if the status code changes. In addition, it should change when the substantive content of the structure definition changes."

fields.name: _date
fields.descr: "Extensions for date"

fields.name: publisher
fields.descr: "The name of the individual or organization that published the structure definition."

fields.name: _publisher
fields.descr: "Extensions for publisher"

fields.name: contact
fields.descr: "Contact details to assist a user in finding and communicating with the publisher."

fields.name: description
fields.descr: "A free text natural language description of the structure definition from a consumer's perspective."

fields.name: _description
fields.descr: "Extensions for description"

fields.name: useContext
fields.descr: "The content was developed with a focus and intent of supporting the contexts that are listed. These terms may be used to assist with indexing and searching for appropriate structure definition instances."

fields.name: jurisdiction
fields.descr: "A legal or geographic region in which the structure definition is intended to be used."

fields.name: purpose
fields.descr: "Explaination of why this structure definition is needed and why it has been designed as it has."

fields.name: _purpose
fields.descr: "Extensions for purpose"

fields.name: copyright
fields.descr: "A copyright statement relating to the structure definition and/or its contents. Copyright statements are generally legal restrictions on the use and publishing of the structure definition."

fields.name: _copyright
fields.descr: "Extensions for copyright"

fields.name: keyword
fields.descr: "A set of key words or terms from external terminologies that may be used to assist with indexing and searching of templates."

fields.name: fhirVersion
fields.descr: "The version of the FHIR specification on which this StructureDefinition is based - this is the formal version of the specification, without the revision number, e.g. [publication].[major].[minor], which is 3.0.1 for this version."

fields.name: _fhirVersion
fields.descr: "Extensions for fhirVersion"

fields.name: mapping
fields.descr: "An external specification that the content is mapped to."

fields.name: kind
fields.descr: "Defines the kind of structure that this definition is describing."

fields.name: _kind
fields.descr: "Extensions for kind"

fields.name: FHIRabstract
fields.descr: "Whether structure this definition describes is abstract or not  - that is, whether the structure is not intended to be instantiated. For Resources and Data types, abstract types will never be exchanged  between systems."

fields.name: _abstract
fields.descr: "Extensions for abstract"

fields.name: contextType
fields.descr: "If this is an extension, Identifies the context within FHIR resources where the extension can be used."

fields.name: _contextType
fields.descr: "Extensions for contextType"

fields.name: context
fields.descr: "Identifies the types of resource or data type elements to which the extension can be applied."

fields.name: _context
fields.descr: "Extensions for context"

fields.name: contextInvariant
fields.descr: "A set of rules as Fluent Invariants about when the extension can be used (e.g. co-occurrence variants for the extension)."

fields.name: _contextInvariant
fields.descr: "Extensions for contextInvariant"

fields.name: type
fields.descr: "The type this structure describes. If the derivation kind is 'specialization' then this is the master definition for a type, and there is always one of these (a data type, an extension, a resource, including abstract ones). Otherwise the structure definition is a constraint on the stated type (and in this case, the type cannot be an abstract type)."

fields.name: _type
fields.descr: "Extensions for type"

fields.name: baseDefinition
fields.descr: "An absolute URI that is the base structure from which this type is derived, either by specialization or constraint."

fields.name: _baseDefinition
fields.descr: "Extensions for baseDefinition"

fields.name: derivation
fields.descr: "How the type relates to the baseDefinition."

fields.name: _derivation
fields.descr: "Extensions for derivation"

fields.name: snapshot
fields.descr: "A snapshot view is expressed in a stand alone form that can be used and interpreted without considering the base StructureDefinition."

fields.name: differential
fields.descr: "A differential view is expressed relative to the base StructureDefinition - a statement of differences that it applies."

fields.name: text
fields.descr:
"A human-readable narrative that contains a summary of the resource, and may be used to represent the content of the resource to a human. The narrative need not encode all the structured data, but is required to contain sufficient detail to make it \"clinically safe\" for a human to just read the narrative. Resource definitions may define what content should be represented in the narrative to ensure clinical safety."
